The presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Atiku Abubakar, yesterday held a meeting with a former military president, General Ibrahim Badamasi Babangida. Our correspondent gathered that the meeting took place at Babangida’s uphill residence in Minna, Niger State. Presidential poll aftermath: NSCIA cautions against incitement Atiku charges Gadzama, 18 other SANs to reclaim mandate, strengthen democracy Atiku arrived at the Minna airport by 11 am and was received by a former Governor of Niger State, Dr Mu’azu Babangida Aliyu, before he proceeded to the uphill mansion of the former head of state. A source said the visit was in connection with the outcome of the February 25, presidential election in which Atiku came second according to the result declared by INEC.